text.tspan: Agriculture value added per worker vs. GDP per capita, 1991 to 2019
Agriculture value added per worker versus gross domestic product (GDP) per capita, both measured in constant
US$. Agriculture value added per worker is a measure of agricultural productivity. It corresponds to the ratio between
value added in agriculture and number of people employed in agriculture.
Agriculture value added per worker (constant 2015 US$)
Source: World Bank based on data from multiple sources
